\begin_layout Subsection
Coin collector
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This game mode is focused on providing the user with an auto generated route,
 this was implemented by using the algorithm described in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:Random-route-implementation"

\end_inset

.
 During the route the user is provided with some milestones, in this case
 coins.
 The coins are the sound sources that the user will be guided to by following
 the audio feedback, see ch 3.1.
 When the user gets close to the coin, it is collected and the user will
 hear a confirmation sound and be guided to the next coin.
 The route ends when the last coin is collected or when the user manually
 finishes the game session.
 During the game session the a timer is keeping track of the time, it is
 possible for the user to pause and resume during the session.
 By using the information from the GPS, see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sub:GPS"

\end_inset

, data on the users movement is collected to calculate the total running
 distance.
 This information, time and distance, is used to calculate information about
 the users speed and pace.
 When the user collects a coin, information on the distance and time in
 that moment is stored, to allow the user to see exactly when each coin
 is collected.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All the information that is accumulated and calculated while the user is
 running is available in the screen for the user to see a any moment during
 the game session.
 But the information is also stored in the database that is described in
 
