\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Tutorial
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The tutorial was implemented to allow the user to try the application and
 become familiar with how the sound works without actually making the user
 go out and run.
 While holding the device in the hand and looking at the screen, the user
 will see an arrow that spins around accordingly to how the device is rotated
 in their hands.
 This is done by using the gyroscope sensor that was implemented into the
 application, see 3.2.
 Somewhere on the screen is a sound source hidden and when the user spins
 the arrow the sound will guide them to the sound source in the same manner
 as in the coin collector mode.
 When the user thinks it is heading in the right direction he/she can push
 the run button, this simulates moving forward in the coin collector mode.
 
\end_layout

